owAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pulling With Nullify (Part 2)</span><hr size=1> You can single pull mobs 10 levels lower than you at 60.  Im pretty sure that applies as far back as 52...not sure if that scales down from there or not.  Sooo, in seb, you can single pull the mobs just so long as all the mobs in the cluster around the one you are pulling are 10 levels lower than you or more.  They can be ontop of eachother and this rule applies.<br>
<br>
As for nullify, its the second least aggro means of pulling.  Distance aggro pulling is the least aggroing, but is difficult to judge if you are going to add more than 1 due to your distance.  Dedbuffing the mob (tash/malo/slow) is the next lowest aggro on pull (mind you Im talking about aggro shared, not aggro generated on the mob).  Lastly damaging the mob is the highest aggro.<br>
<br>
Everything is aggro distance based.  If two mobs are on top of eachother, and you are 10+ levels higher, you can single pull.  If they are slightly apart, 9 levels higher and annual will probably work.  If you nuked when they were only slightly apart, you will probably get both.  The closer or lower that the level of the mob, the larger the shared aggro range is on that mob when aggroed.<br>
<br>
Kinda long winded, but thats how aggro works. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urazha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Razha</A> at: 6/19/02 9:31:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uttamartificer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ttam Artificer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(6/26/02 12:55:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pulling</span><hr size=1> Remember also.....your spell casting inherantly produces a certain amount of aggro ....i.e casting next to a mob will aggro the mob.....i know this is true with nukes but uncertain about null...will give it a shot tonight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umariomax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MarioMax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(7/1/02 7:54:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   NOT with Underbulks!</span><hr size=1> 47 Mage trying to pull Underbulks in Echo Caverns. The first set of spawns by the guards is quite easy to singe-pull and wipe out, so I went to the next set deeper in. My first attempt to pull failed (Malisement), so I gated to safety, then tried again using Nullify. Before I knew it, I was on a CR.<br>
